Description: Part of a redware pottery jar joined with other sections to form a single object with a bulbous body, two small pierced handles and decorated with an incised groove and a ridge near the rim. See the fuller description under 1887,0101.849.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, Findspot 55, by great wall south of the "Qasr"
Curator's comments: The Findspot number 55 has been scratched into the side of the jar. Attached to 1887,0101.849, 1887,0101.854, 1887,0101.855. See also London, BM, EA 22324, and Boston MFA 87.632 & 87.634 (TO BE CHECKED)
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 64, 66 § 61, pl. xxxiv, 28)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.93, p.97, p.104, p.192, pl.34, p.216, pl.58)
